curl https://workflowy.com/api/auth -d email="$mail" -d allowSignup=false &> /dev/null
if [ "$?" = 0 ]; then echo Please check your inbox ! fi

[{"title":"Login with password","arg":"password","subtitle":"Login with one time code"},{"title":"Use one time code","arg":"use-code","subtitle":"login with one time code"},{"title":"Send one time code","arg":"send-code","subtitle":"send one time code"}]
on alfred_script(q) tell application "Workflowy" to activate end alfred_script
on alfred_script(q) tell application "Google Chrome" to return URL of active tab of front window end alfred_script
on alfred_script(q) tell application "Google Chrome" to return title of active tab of front window end alfred_script

Use wlogin to autentificate to your workflowy account.
There are many available shortcuts: - wf: search your workflowy workspace - wh: display your home page - ws/wm/wt/wl: show starred/mentions/tags/links - wbm: bookmark a chrome tab
Many shortcuts can be suffixed with a c in orderto include completed nodes in results.
On each node, you can: - Use tab to display child nodes directly in alfred - use enter to open in browser - use alt+enter to add a child to the selected node - use cmd+enter to open in desktop app - use shift+enter to open embed link, or tap shift to preview it. - use cmd+l to show a node note, and cmd+c to open it
